  "body": "Issue within epic #7234 \r\n\r\n# Problem\r\nWe've received more than one report of people struggling to add contacts. An explicit `Invite friends` button on the Contact screen can support users that are accustomed to inviting friends before starting a chat\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n- Add an invite friends button to the Contacts screen\r\n- Invite friends button generates referral url\r\n\r\nDesigns on [Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/TNCyHKtR3sx5EL6YznFWUa4O/Profile?node-id=510%3A4233) \r\n<img width=\"375\" alt=\"Profile -_ Contacts\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35233054/86114727-3cd5e680-bacb-11ea-96d7-43cf36c11981.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\nFollow design on Figma\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\nAdding contacts is not center stage in the UI as starting a chat does not require 'friending' or 'being contacts'. `Contacts` rather serves as a phonebook. Adding an explicit `Invite friends` button to the `Contacts` view, makes starting a chat easier for those under the impression that it is required.\r\n\r\n## Future Steps\r\nAdd remaining features to contact management as found in the design and epic #7234 \r\n",
